  <h2><i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"></i> Overview</h2>

  <p>Engines is for running your own server. Use it to self-host server software and store data. Create a cloud environment that you own and control.</p>

  <h3>Simple</h3>
  <p>Engines has a web interface for managing your server. Applications are straightforward to install, configure and maintain. Back-ups are simple to set-up and run.</p>

  <h3>Flexible</h3>
  <p>Install Engines on a hosted virtual computer, or put it on a personal computer in the office or at home. Access different software packages via the offical Engines library as well as third-party libraries.</p>

  <h3>Powerful</h3>
  <p>Run all your server applications in a single environment. Connect applications, files and devices, and share with friends, contacts, empoyees and colleagues.</p>

  <h3>Secure and private</h3>
  <p>Applications run in sandboxed containers to protect your server from malicious and defective software. You hold the keys to your system and its logs. Domicile in the jurisdiction that makes most sense for you. Run VPN for extra protection.</p>

  <h3>Software</h3>
  <p>Use Engines for hosting email, serving files, media libraries, online stores, personal social feeds, blogs and wikis, VPN end-point browsing, instant messaging, multiplayer gaming, managing projects, CRM, fleet tracking, voip, accounting, document sharing, group contacts and calendar, ERP, student portfolios, and more.</p>
  <p>If your favorite software is not shown in the library, or if you're a software developer that would like to have your application added to Engines, please <%= link_to content_tag(:i, nil, class: "fa fa-pencil") + " get in touch", contact_info_pages_path(), class: "trigger-response-modal" %> and let us know.</p>
